{"TopicId":220310,"ForumId":201,"TopicTitle":"Zooming the camera out does not check for terrain.","CreatedByName":"AzuryxxVORTEX","CreatedById":229641,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-26T23:20:37Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AzuryxxVORTEX","CreatedById":229641,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-26T23:20:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Microsoft Windows 11 Home 10.0.22621 64-bit | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 5 5600H with Radeon Graphics (12) | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3050 Laptop GPU (3977MB) | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E15711\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESeverity\u003C/strong\u003E - Low\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EFrequency\u003C/strong\u003E - Can repeat constantly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E- When rotating the camera around, it is blocked by terrain. If you zoom out into it though, it isn\u0027t blocked and goes right through, exposing the planet\u0027s invisible crust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EHow to replicate\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0-\u003Cbr\u003E\n1. Get into any flight where terrain is present\u003Cbr\u003E\n2. Scroll down with the terrain right behind the camera\u003Cbr\u003E\n3. Observe the underside of the planet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ipslightbox=\u0022\u0022 alt=\u0022Screenshot2023-10-27011949.png.cb2ccb6b5\u002